jtgrimes:
I think having a separate function named inGroupNamed() makes for slightly more readable code, but that's an aesthetic preference.  Both ways work well.
. I think `Sentry::user()->findById()` is confusing, since people would probably expect a `user()` function to return a User object.  The way I implemented this was just to have the Sentry class call its providers directly instead of sending them back to the user.  For example:

```
class Sentry {
...
   public function findUserById($id)
   {
       return $this->userProvider->findById($id);
   } 
...
}
```
